Call Volume Distribution Guidelines
For each outage event, distribute calls as follows:
Time-based Call Distribution:
 
First 15 minutes: 40% of total calls (high surge)
15-30 minutes: 30% of total calls (continued high volume)
30-45 minutes: 20% of total calls (declining)
45-60 minutes: 7% of total calls (tapering off)
60+ minutes: 3% of total calls (residual)
 
Example for Outage Event 1 (219 customers in Dallas):
 
10:15-10:30 AM: ~88 calls (40%)
10:30-10:45 AM: ~66 calls (30%)
10:45-11:00 AM: ~44 calls (20%)
11:00-11:15 AM: ~15 calls (7%)
11:15-11:32 AM: ~6 calls (3%)

Example for Outage Event 2 (126 customers in Bridgeport):

1:11-1:26 PM: ~50 calls (40%)
1:26-1:41 PM: ~38 calls (30%)
1:41-1:56 PM: ~25 calls (20%)
1:56-2:11 PM: ~9 calls (7%)
2:11-2:21 PM: ~4 calls (3%)
